1
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:15,375
[MABU] Let desire flow.
Every last drop.

2
00:00:15,458 --> 00:00:18,875
The future belongs to those
who can connect their desires.

3
00:00:18,958 --> 00:00:20,916
Never let it go.

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,625
Reo.

5
00:00:23,958 --> 00:00:26,416
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
Otter, actually.

6
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:28,541
[MABU]
Do I know you?

7
00:00:28,625 --> 00:00:30,291
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
No, but you will soon,

8
00:00:30,375 --> 00:00:33,875
because you have been reborn
as my precious little doll.

9
00:00:33,958 --> 00:00:37,250
-[MABU] Can I see Reo?
-Why, of course.

10
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:41,416
In fact, I'm sure he'll be
"otterly" ecstatic to visit you.

11
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:43,625
But before we proceed,

12
00:00:43,708 --> 00:00:46,000
I'm afraid there's
one condition.

13
00:02:15,958 --> 00:02:18,875
[KEPPI] I can't guarantee
that you'll survive.

14
00:02:18,958 --> 00:02:22,666
Are you certain that you want
to fight for the Dishes of Hope?

15
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:25,833
-[KAZUKI] I've made my choice.
-Kazuki.

16
00:02:27,041 --> 00:02:28,416
-[ALL gasp]
-[exploding]

17
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:29,666
[thudding]

18
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:32,208
[grunts, groans]

19
00:02:32,291 --> 00:02:33,291
[stomps]

20
00:02:33,375 --> 00:02:34,833
[KAZUKI, ENTA]
Keppi!

21
00:02:34,916 --> 00:02:37,291
[REO] You won't be able to hide
from me anymore.

22
00:02:37,375 --> 00:02:41,791
And by the way, that anti-otter
barrier won't save you.

23
00:02:41,875 --> 00:02:44,333
'Cause Mabu and I are kappa.

24
00:02:44,416 --> 00:02:46,291
-[KAZUKI] No way.
-[KEPPI] Indeed.

25
00:02:46,375 --> 00:02:48,666
Moreover, they were
once my vassals.

26
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:50,083
Reo, why are you--

27
00:02:50,166 --> 00:02:51,458
-[KEPPI grunts]
-[REO scoffs]

28
00:02:51,541 --> 00:02:54,916
[REO] Hand over the Dish
and I'll be on my way.

29
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,875
You know I'm not
afraid to shoot.

30
00:02:56,958 --> 00:02:58,583
No. You're not going
to get a damn thing!

31
00:02:58,666 --> 00:03:01,041
Give us back what you stole!

32
00:03:01,125 --> 00:03:02,708
[ENTA]
Kazuki. [gasps]

33
00:03:02,791 --> 00:03:04,083
It's you.

34
00:03:04,166 --> 00:03:07,000
Looks like you survived
that gunshot after all!

35
00:03:07,083 --> 00:03:08,750
Only four hours left.

36
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:10,208
-[ENTA gasps]
-Too bad.

37
00:03:10,291 --> 00:03:12,208
It seems you'll
never see the dawn.

38
00:03:12,291 --> 00:03:14,916
-Just four hours?
-We don't have time!

39
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,250
Give us the dishes now!

40
00:03:16,333 --> 00:03:18,750
[REO chuckles]

41
00:03:18,833 --> 00:03:22,333
So we both need them
for a special someone, huh?

42
00:03:22,416 --> 00:03:24,250
All right, come along.

43
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:26,500
[ENTA]
Four hours? Four hours!

44
00:03:26,583 --> 00:03:28,750
Only four hours!

45
00:03:28,833 --> 00:03:31,000
[KAZUKI]
I promise I'll save you.

46
00:03:31,083 --> 00:03:33,083
Please, just believe in me.

47
00:03:33,166 --> 00:03:36,208
-[ENTA] Thank you.
-Well, you're optimistic.

48
00:03:36,291 --> 00:03:38,750
But you're a slave to
your desires like anyone else.

49
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:40,166
Once they're dangled
in front of you,

50
00:03:40,250 --> 00:03:42,708
you'll throw away
your connection.

51
00:03:42,791 --> 00:03:46,125
I'm here to protect our
connection. Not throw it away!

52
00:03:46,208 --> 00:03:49,250
I'm fighting for our future
together!

53
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:50,958
[REO growls]

54
00:03:51,041 --> 00:03:53,291
You dumb brats
don't know anything.

55
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:06,041
-[REO] Mabu!
-Prince Keppi.

56
00:04:06,125 --> 00:04:09,541
[KEPPI] Mabu, please talk
some sense into Reo.

57
00:04:09,625 --> 00:04:11,791
Let's sing together again,
like old times!

58
00:04:11,875 --> 00:04:13,541
You know the song!

59
00:04:13,625 --> 00:04:15,458
What's the point?

60
00:04:15,541 --> 00:04:17,916
I fear I'm no longer the man
that you desire.

61
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,916
So you finally admit it, then.

62
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,333
You're nothing but somebody's
half-baked doll.

63
00:04:22,416 --> 00:04:26,166
Reo, the Otter knows about
the Dishes of Hope.

64
00:04:27,208 --> 00:04:29,875
He read my memories.
I could not resist him.

65
00:04:29,958 --> 00:04:32,916
[gasps]
Oh, come on.

66
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:36,041
How many times are you gonna
let me down, huh?

67
00:04:36,125 --> 00:04:38,666
How many times are
you gonna betray me?

68
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:40,791
[ENTA, KAZUKI]
Let's go!

69
00:04:40,875 --> 00:04:42,416
[BOTH grunt]

70
00:04:43,875 --> 00:04:46,083
-[KEPPI] Kero. Kero.
-[KAZUKI, ENTA panting]

71
00:04:46,166 --> 00:04:47,541
[REO gasps]

72
00:04:50,916 --> 00:04:52,208
Reo.

73
00:04:52,291 --> 00:04:53,958
I don't wanna hear it.

74
00:04:54,041 --> 00:04:55,583
I've suffered enough.

75
00:04:55,666 --> 00:04:58,666
Listen. I didn't mean to--
[gasps]

76
00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:00,125
Don't touch me!

77
00:05:00,208 --> 00:05:02,458
And stop pretending
to be my Mabu.

78
00:05:02,541 --> 00:05:05,083
You aren't the man who found me
when I was all alone.

79
00:05:05,166 --> 00:05:07,958
You never told me those
sweet words I longed to hear!

80
00:05:08,041 --> 00:05:09,416
[MABU gasps]

81
00:05:20,791 --> 00:05:22,500
[MABU]
It hurts.

82
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:27,833
We've finally
reached the bottom.

83
00:05:34,916 --> 00:05:37,041
The dishes!

84
00:05:37,125 --> 00:05:38,750
[energy shimmering]

85
00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:42,375
[DARK KEPPI]
Dadadadadadadadadadada.

86
00:05:42,458 --> 00:05:44,000
Da-Darkness!

87
00:05:44,083 --> 00:05:46,666
-[gasps]
-So we're reunited at last,

88
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:47,791
Dark Keppi!

89
00:05:47,875 --> 00:05:49,875
-Dark Keppi?
-Indeed.

90
00:05:49,958 --> 00:05:51,375
He is the despair I felt

91
00:05:51,458 --> 00:05:53,708
when I was captured
by the Otters.

92
00:05:53,791 --> 00:05:58,041
During the war, I broke
my own shirikodama in half

93
00:05:58,125 --> 00:05:59,958
to spare myself
from the hopelessness

94
00:06:00,041 --> 00:06:01,916
that threatened to overtake me.

95
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,791
[KAZUKI]
Then he's you?

96
00:06:03,875 --> 00:06:06,625
[KEPPI]
He's my pain. My other half.

97
00:06:06,708 --> 00:06:09,375
I have come here to reunite
with him, so that I may be whole

98
00:06:09,458 --> 00:06:11,708
and do battle
with the Otters once more.

99
00:06:11,791 --> 00:06:13,375
[KAZUKI]
What exactly are they?

100
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:17,083
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
A fine question.

101
00:06:17,166 --> 00:06:20,750
We are a manifestation
of your deepest desires.

102
00:06:20,833 --> 00:06:22,291
-[KAZUKI gasps]
-[KAZUKI, ENTA gasp]

103
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:24,458
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
We are one and we are many.

104
00:06:24,541 --> 00:06:28,083
We are formless and we are the
shape of what you long for most.

105
00:06:28,166 --> 00:06:29,708
You are wicked!

106
00:06:29,791 --> 00:06:31,916
What've you done
to Reo and Mabu?

107
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:35,458
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
How "otterly" uncalled for!

108
00:06:35,541 --> 00:06:37,416
Why, I liberated them!

109
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:39,375
[KEPPI]
Lies, as usual!

110
00:06:39,458 --> 00:06:41,791
You seduced them
when they were vulnerable!

111
00:06:41,875 --> 00:06:43,208
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
What do you care?

112
00:06:43,291 --> 00:06:44,833
He was already broken.

113
00:06:44,916 --> 00:06:46,458
It was so easy.

114
00:06:46,541 --> 00:06:48,583
-Like this!
-[whooshing]

115
00:06:48,666 --> 00:06:50,125
What the hell?

116
00:06:50,208 --> 00:06:52,541
Oh, God, that hurts!

117
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:54,750
[KAZUKI, KEPPI]
Enta!

118
00:06:54,833 --> 00:06:56,791
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
Your precious Dishes of Hope

119
00:06:56,875 --> 00:06:58,458
belong to me now.

120
00:06:58,541 --> 00:07:02,458
Nothing but despair remains
in a world of never beginning,

121
00:07:02,541 --> 00:07:05,250
never ending,
and never connecting.

122
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:08,333
A world where I have
"otter" control.

123
00:07:09,875 --> 00:07:11,375
[groans softly]

124
00:07:11,458 --> 00:07:13,166
Where am I?

125
00:07:20,375 --> 00:07:22,041
Kazuki.

126
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,625
[KAZUKI ILLUSION] You don't mind
giving all those Dishes of Hope

127
00:07:25,708 --> 00:07:28,333
-to me, now do you, Enta?
-Huh?

128
00:07:28,416 --> 00:07:30,291
[KAZUKI ILLUSION] 'Cause we're
more than just friends,

129
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:31,541
after all.

130
00:07:31,625 --> 00:07:33,041
[ENTA] Yeah, uh, totally!

131
00:07:33,125 --> 00:07:35,958
I mean, we're the Golden Duo!

132
00:07:36,041 --> 00:07:38,583
[KAZUKI ILLUSION]
Then prove it to me.

133
00:07:38,666 --> 00:07:40,625
Bring them together.

134
00:07:42,166 --> 00:07:45,583
Anything for you, Kazuki.

135
00:07:45,666 --> 00:07:47,541
Hey, Enta?

136
00:07:47,625 --> 00:07:51,000
♪

137
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:58,166
[energy shimmering]

138
00:07:58,250 --> 00:07:59,958
Snap out of it!

139
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,500
[KAZUKI]
Enta, stop!

140
00:08:06,583 --> 00:08:09,250
[KAZUKI ILLUSION]
That's so sweet of you, Enta.

141
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:12,166
You're the best.
Forget the Golden Duo.

142
00:08:12,250 --> 00:08:14,625
Now we can become
something much more.

143
00:08:14,708 --> 00:08:16,041
[ENTA gasps]

144
00:08:16,125 --> 00:08:17,625
[shattering]

145
00:08:17,708 --> 00:08:21,291
I won't risk what we have after
I fought to get it back!

146
00:08:21,375 --> 00:08:23,416
[strained grunting]

147
00:08:24,666 --> 00:08:26,458
[KAZUKI grunts]

148
00:08:26,541 --> 00:08:28,958
Are you okay?
Come on, talk to me!

149
00:08:29,041 --> 00:08:32,250
Sorry.
Looks like I broke the Dish.

150
00:08:32,333 --> 00:08:33,958
[KAZUKI]
There's no time.

151
00:08:34,041 --> 00:08:35,250
Hey, Keppi!

152
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:36,833
-Take my shirikodama--
-[ENTA] Shut up!

153
00:08:36,916 --> 00:08:37,791
Aah!

154
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:41,083
You really think some lame-ass
self-sacrifice

155
00:08:41,166 --> 00:08:43,125
-is gonna make me happy?
-[KAZUKI] But--

156
00:08:43,208 --> 00:08:46,750
Kazuki, our bond
won't be broken, no matter what.

157
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:48,500
If you try to make me forget,

158
00:08:48,583 --> 00:08:50,208
then I'll haunt you
in your next life!

159
00:08:51,666 --> 00:08:53,291
Then you still believe
in our future?

160
00:08:53,375 --> 00:08:56,875
We'll be the Golden Duo forever.

161
00:08:56,958 --> 00:08:59,083
[gasps, then screams]

162
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:02,375
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
A lovely sentiment,

163
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:05,083
but meaningless now
that I have the dishes.

164
00:09:05,166 --> 00:09:07,333
[gunshot]

165
00:09:07,416 --> 00:09:08,875
Like hell you do.

166
00:09:08,958 --> 00:09:11,458
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
Reo, if you don't "otter" up

167
00:09:11,541 --> 00:09:14,875
the dishes to me,
I can't guarantee Mabu's safety.

168
00:09:14,958 --> 00:09:16,625
I don't care
about your damn doll!

169
00:09:16,708 --> 00:09:17,916
With my wish,

170
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,125
I'm gonna bring back
the real Mabu!

171
00:09:20,208 --> 00:09:23,333
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
You accuse me of "disottersty?"

172
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:26,166
Then perhaps I should
show you the truth!

173
00:09:27,833 --> 00:09:30,500
The time has come to grant
your wish, Mabu.

174
00:09:30,583 --> 00:09:33,333
Why don't you show us
what that is?

175
00:09:36,958 --> 00:09:37,958
[bursting]

176
00:09:38,958 --> 00:09:41,500
[MABU] I thought as long
as I could be by your side,

177
00:09:41,583 --> 00:09:43,333
nothing else would matter.

178
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:46,666
But now that I know
I'll never win your heart back,

179
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,416
I feel so empty.

180
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:53,000
At least let me indulge
in my selfish desires.

181
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:56,958
I have nothing else.

182
00:09:59,458 --> 00:10:00,458
[REO gasps]

183
00:10:03,958 --> 00:10:05,208
[energy rushing]

184
00:10:05,291 --> 00:10:07,916
[REO]
Mabu!

185
00:10:08,916 --> 00:10:11,166
[MALE VOICE]
Result. Desire.

186
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:12,625
Mabu. Transform.

187
00:10:12,708 --> 00:10:14,583
[splashing]

188
00:10:14,666 --> 00:10:16,583
Why?

189
00:10:16,666 --> 00:10:19,583
[bubbling]

190
00:10:19,666 --> 00:10:21,541
What the hell are you thinking?

191
00:10:21,625 --> 00:10:25,000
Damn it! Why would you do this
to yourself?

192
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:27,833
[KEPPI]
You must be stout of heart, Reo.

193
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:29,375
You'll find your answer

194
00:10:29,458 --> 00:10:31,708
if you have the courage
to face his desire.

195
00:10:31,791 --> 00:10:33,958
Damn it.

196
00:10:34,041 --> 00:10:36,000
-[gunshot]
-[KEPPI grunts]

197
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,458
Let's go!

198
00:10:40,541 --> 00:10:43,208
[KEPPI]
Now, sing that song once again!

199
00:10:43,291 --> 00:10:44,583
[KEPPI, REO yelling]

200
00:10:44,666 --> 00:10:48,125
♪

201
00:10:50,541 --> 00:10:53,125
♪ Time to take back
what I need ♪

202
00:10:53,208 --> 00:10:55,500
♪ I can't leave
'til I retrieve it ♪

203
00:10:55,583 --> 00:10:57,166
[MABU ZOMBIE]
♪ Our connection ♪

204
00:10:57,250 --> 00:11:00,500
♪ It hides a secret
that I won't let anybody see ♪

205
00:11:00,583 --> 00:11:03,791
♪ Time to take back
what I need ♪

206
00:11:03,875 --> 00:11:06,166
♪ I can't leave
'til I retrieve it ♪

207
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:07,500
[MABU]
♪ Our connection ♪

208
00:11:07,583 --> 00:11:10,500
♪ Deadly secrets hiding
in my history ♪

209
00:11:10,583 --> 00:11:12,625
[MABU ZOMBIE]
♪ Mystery! ♪

210
00:11:12,708 --> 00:11:14,000
♪ Carry on through! ♪

211
00:11:14,083 --> 00:11:17,041
[REO]
♪ How can I connect to you? ♪

212
00:11:17,125 --> 00:11:23,000
[MABU ZOMBIE] Share your love,
even if it isn't true.

213
00:11:23,083 --> 00:11:28,375
♪ Deep inside your desire's
calling me ♪

214
00:11:28,458 --> 00:11:33,500
♪ Dive in and then set it free ♪

215
00:11:33,583 --> 00:11:36,541
[MABU ZOMBIE]
♪ Give it to me! ♪

216
00:11:36,625 --> 00:11:39,250
♪ Ride the waves
into the fray ♪

217
00:11:39,333 --> 00:11:41,625
♪ Seize the truth buried away ♪

218
00:11:41,708 --> 00:11:44,208
♪ Is it love? I can't say ♪

219
00:11:44,291 --> 00:11:47,083
[MABU ZOMBIE]
♪ Until I tear it from you ♪

220
00:11:47,166 --> 00:11:49,541
[REO] ♪ Souls combine,
stack up the plates ♪

221
00:11:49,625 --> 00:11:50,875
♪ Mystic ball ♪

222
00:11:50,958 --> 00:11:52,333
[MABU ZOMBIE]
♪ Deciding our fates! ♪

223
00:11:52,416 --> 00:11:54,916
♪ Our wishes ♪

224
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,875
♪ Our dishes ♪

225
00:11:57,958 --> 00:12:00,166
[REO, MABU ZOMBIE]
Sarazanmai!

226
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:01,416
[grunts]

227
00:12:02,458 --> 00:12:06,166
-[energy bursting]
-I've still got it, baby!

228
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:08,125
[shimmering]

229
00:12:08,208 --> 00:12:09,708
-[energy bursting]
-[rain pouring]

230
00:12:10,708 --> 00:12:13,791
This is it.
This is Mabu's desire.

231
00:12:17,625 --> 00:12:19,791
[IMPERIAL BOSS] I'm afraid
there's one condition.

232
00:12:19,875 --> 00:12:22,583
You must give up
your connection to Reo.

233
00:12:23,958 --> 00:12:25,583
Connections are poison.

234
00:12:25,666 --> 00:12:28,541
If you express a single word
of love to Reo,

235
00:12:28,625 --> 00:12:32,833
your heart will explode,
leaving behind nothing but ash.

236
00:12:32,916 --> 00:12:34,958
Then your peaceful existence
together

237
00:12:35,041 --> 00:12:37,208
will come
to a violent conclusion.

238
00:12:37,291 --> 00:12:38,500
But why?

239
00:12:38,583 --> 00:12:40,083
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
Tell me you hate him.

240
00:12:40,166 --> 00:12:42,125
That you despise him.

241
00:12:42,208 --> 00:12:44,416
[MABU]
I want to connect with Reo.

242
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:46,458
I want to stay by his side.

243
00:12:46,541 --> 00:12:48,875
No matter what,
I can't leave him.

244
00:12:48,958 --> 00:12:51,166
I need you.

245
00:12:51,250 --> 00:12:52,833
Reo.

246
00:12:52,916 --> 00:12:54,458
Reo!

247
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:57,916
I hate him.

248
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,458
I despise Reo.

249
00:12:59,541 --> 00:13:01,625
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
Such a good boy.

250
00:13:01,708 --> 00:13:05,958
Now I believe a private
baking session is in "otter."

251
00:13:06,041 --> 00:13:08,625
[MABU]
This is for Reo.

252
00:13:08,708 --> 00:13:10,458
For our future.

253
00:13:10,541 --> 00:13:13,000
Mabu chose to give up
our connection,

254
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:15,083
so that we could be together?

255
00:13:15,166 --> 00:13:18,416
[MABU ZOMBIE] Finally.
I've told Reo the truth.

256
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:21,041
[energy exploding]

257
00:13:22,708 --> 00:13:25,041
[waves crashing]

258
00:13:26,708 --> 00:13:28,625
Mabu.

259
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:30,416
-[grunts]
-[flops]

260
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:31,833
[REO]
It's you!

261
00:13:31,916 --> 00:13:33,291
You're alive!

262
00:13:33,375 --> 00:13:34,500
What happened?

263
00:13:34,583 --> 00:13:35,875
Let's hurry.

264
00:13:35,958 --> 00:13:37,625
We must deliver that
to the prince.

265
00:13:37,708 --> 00:13:39,708
Hey, wait a sec.
We need to talk!

266
00:13:39,791 --> 00:13:44,666
I thought you were a traitor,
a broken doll, a fake.

267
00:13:44,750 --> 00:13:45,750
Now what?

268
00:13:45,833 --> 00:13:46,833
Damn it all!

269
00:13:46,916 --> 00:13:48,083
Mabu!

270
00:13:48,166 --> 00:13:49,250
Sara!

271
00:13:49,333 --> 00:13:51,166
[BOTH]
Sara!

272
00:13:51,250 --> 00:13:53,291
Sarazanmai!

273
00:13:53,375 --> 00:13:55,208
♪

274
00:13:55,291 --> 00:13:57,750
[energy bursting]

275
00:14:03,750 --> 00:14:05,916
[energy shimmering]

276
00:14:07,541 --> 00:14:09,291
[REO screaming]

277
00:14:09,375 --> 00:14:10,750
[MALE VOICE]
Leaking.

278
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:13,416
♪

279
00:14:15,041 --> 00:14:16,750
Mabu.

280
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:19,000
My wish came true.
You really are alive!

281
00:14:19,083 --> 00:14:21,916
[MABU]
I hate him. I despise Reo.

282
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,166
[REO gasps]

283
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:25,208
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
Such a good boy.

284
00:14:25,291 --> 00:14:30,125
Now I believe a private
baking session is in "otter."

285
00:14:31,541 --> 00:14:34,333
[REO] There's no way Mabu would
betray me for some Otter!

286
00:14:34,416 --> 00:14:36,041
It can't be him! Liar!

287
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:39,125
The Mabu I know would never look
at me like that!

288
00:14:39,208 --> 00:14:41,458
Do you really think you can
trick me that easily?

289
00:14:41,541 --> 00:14:43,000
He's betraying me again.

290
00:14:43,083 --> 00:14:45,791
With that calm look on his face,
like nothing's wrong.

291
00:14:45,875 --> 00:14:48,041
All his emotions
spilled right out.

292
00:14:48,125 --> 00:14:49,916
Like a broken doll.

293
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,541
-[pounding]
-[grunts]

294
00:14:51,625 --> 00:14:53,708
Screw this crap.

295
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:56,000
What the hell do you know?

296
00:14:56,083 --> 00:14:57,541
I was a fool.

297
00:14:57,625 --> 00:14:59,291
How could I treat him like that?

298
00:14:59,375 --> 00:15:00,791
[gasps]

299
00:15:00,875 --> 00:15:02,458
♪

300
00:15:02,541 --> 00:15:04,708
There's something that
I need to tell you, Reo.

301
00:15:04,791 --> 00:15:06,083
It's time.

302
00:15:06,166 --> 00:15:08,583
Stop it! You can't!

303
00:15:08,666 --> 00:15:11,583
You are the one
and only partner for me.

304
00:15:11,666 --> 00:15:13,166
Reo.

305
00:15:13,250 --> 00:15:16,541
From the very beginning,
to the very end.

306
00:15:16,625 --> 00:15:18,458
I will always love you.

307
00:15:18,541 --> 00:15:20,958
[energy shimmering]

308
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:22,958
[REO gasps]

309
00:15:23,041 --> 00:15:25,083
[energy bursting]

310
00:15:25,166 --> 00:15:27,083
[exploding]

311
00:15:27,166 --> 00:15:29,125
♪

312
00:15:30,958 --> 00:15:32,458
[groans, gulps]

313
00:15:32,541 --> 00:15:34,500
[KEPPI]
Desire assimilated.

314
00:15:36,250 --> 00:15:38,083
[hissing]

315
00:15:38,166 --> 00:15:39,625
[KEPPI]
Mabu.

316
00:15:39,708 --> 00:15:43,625
I promise I shall connect
your desire to the future.

317
00:15:52,875 --> 00:15:54,375
Reo.

318
00:15:54,458 --> 00:15:58,208
[laughs]

319
00:15:58,291 --> 00:15:59,666
You think I'm gonna fall

320
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:01,625
for another one of your lies,
you damn Otter?

321
00:16:01,708 --> 00:16:03,583
Well, I know better
and you can't trick me!

322
00:16:03,666 --> 00:16:06,958
The Leaks always
portray the truth.

323
00:16:07,041 --> 00:16:09,583
But I don't need
to tell you that.

324
00:16:09,666 --> 00:16:11,666
[exploding]

325
00:16:14,375 --> 00:16:16,125
[groans]

326
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:17,958
[grunting]

327
00:16:18,041 --> 00:16:19,333
[KAZUKI]
Keppi!

328
00:16:19,416 --> 00:16:20,750
Damn it, Mabu.

329
00:16:20,833 --> 00:16:23,833
You broke your promise
twice now, didn't you?

330
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:26,291
-[firing]
-[exploding]

331
00:16:26,375 --> 00:16:27,833
[exploding]

332
00:16:27,916 --> 00:16:29,375
[gasps]

333
00:16:29,458 --> 00:16:31,166
[crowd yelling]

334
00:16:34,166 --> 00:16:36,583
You've gone and left me behind.

335
00:16:36,666 --> 00:16:38,500
What am I supposed to do?

336
00:16:38,583 --> 00:16:40,666
You tell me I should hold on
to my desire,

337
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:43,125
but I can't do that without you!

338
00:16:43,208 --> 00:16:44,875
[exploding]

339
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,916
[whimpering]

340
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:53,791
Give me the Dish or die.

341
00:16:53,875 --> 00:16:55,708
-No way!
-[KEPPI] Stop it!

342
00:16:55,791 --> 00:16:57,333
Let's just talk this through!

343
00:16:57,416 --> 00:16:59,708
[REO] I'm bringing him back.
Do you hear me?

344
00:16:59,791 --> 00:17:02,291
And I'll kill anyone in my way!

345
00:17:02,375 --> 00:17:03,500
[KAZUKI grunts]

346
00:17:03,583 --> 00:17:04,583
[groans]

347
00:17:04,666 --> 00:17:07,000
[ENTA]
Hey, you all right?

348
00:17:07,083 --> 00:17:09,083
I'm not gonna
give up on my hope!

349
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:10,458
I'm not gonna lose the things

350
00:17:10,541 --> 00:17:12,166
that I love in this world
ever again!

351
00:17:12,250 --> 00:17:14,000
You all piss me off.

352
00:17:14,083 --> 00:17:16,958
Just go to hell already.

353
00:17:17,041 --> 00:17:18,750
Kazuki!

354
00:17:23,958 --> 00:17:25,291
[gasps]

355
00:17:26,458 --> 00:17:30,291
I'm angry, but now
I don't remember why.

356
00:17:30,375 --> 00:17:34,708
I had this burning feeling
in my heart, but for who?

357
00:17:37,458 --> 00:17:38,916
Someone.

358
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:42,041
But now they've just faded away.

359
00:17:47,125 --> 00:17:48,625
What's this?

360
00:17:51,583 --> 00:17:52,875
Reo.

361
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:56,166
I don't... I-I... I...

362
00:17:56,250 --> 00:17:57,333
-[gunshot]
-[grunts]

363
00:17:57,416 --> 00:18:00,333
♪

364
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:05,208
[laughs]

365
00:18:05,291 --> 00:18:07,625
My chest. It hurts.

366
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:13,208
[KAZUKI]
Toi!

367
00:18:14,250 --> 00:18:15,708
Enta!

368
00:18:15,791 --> 00:18:17,416
You're still alive, right?

369
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,625
-[ENTA] Not for long.
-[dishes clattering]

370
00:18:21,291 --> 00:18:23,291
[KEPPI]
Reo, Mabu.

371
00:18:23,375 --> 00:18:25,291
Why don't you rest for a while?

372
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:29,333
[HARUKA] There's this
funny dream I keep having.

373
00:18:29,416 --> 00:18:32,625
I'm riding a giant Nyantaro
in space,

374
00:18:32,708 --> 00:18:34,750
and I meet the Little Prince.

375
00:18:34,833 --> 00:18:36,375
Then the Prince looks at me

376
00:18:36,458 --> 00:18:39,250
and asks me to pick
between love and desire.

377
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:41,375
But I'm too scared
to answer him.

378
00:18:41,458 --> 00:18:43,083
If I pick one,

379
00:18:43,166 --> 00:18:45,875
I'm afraid that the big circle
might break somehow.

380
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:48,916
[SARA] As we speak,
the people of this world

381
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:51,125
are facing a terrible trial.

382
00:18:51,208 --> 00:18:53,125
Are they still connected?

383
00:18:53,208 --> 00:18:56,291
Or has that connection
been broken?

384
00:18:56,375 --> 00:18:59,083
[shattering]

385
00:18:59,166 --> 00:19:01,666
-[gasps]
-[SARA gasps]

386
00:19:04,208 --> 00:19:07,083
[energy whirling]

387
00:19:12,666 --> 00:19:15,333
[KAZUKI]
You came back, after all!

388
00:19:15,416 --> 00:19:17,625
Thank you.

389
00:19:17,708 --> 00:19:19,000
If it wasn't for you,

390
00:19:19,083 --> 00:19:20,625
Kazuki would be d--

391
00:19:20,708 --> 00:19:22,416
-[grunts]
-Enta?

392
00:19:22,500 --> 00:19:25,916
[FEMALE VOICE] Enta's death
will occur in forty seconds.

393
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:29,375
You must hurry and make
your wish before it's too late!

394
00:19:29,458 --> 00:19:31,708
You hand that Dish
over to me now.

395
00:19:33,083 --> 00:19:34,416
[KAZUKI]
Toi?

396
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:36,125
[TOI]
My brother died.

397
00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:39,666
I'm going to use a wish
to bring him back.

398
00:19:44,875 --> 00:19:49,083
[FEMALE VOICE] Enta's death
will occur in 15 seconds.

399
00:19:51,916 --> 00:19:57,916
Ten, nine, eight,
seven, six, five,

400
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:01,958
four, three, two, one.

401
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:41,041
[exploding]

402
00:21:48,791 --> 00:21:50,416
[grunts softly]

403
00:21:51,708 --> 00:21:55,083
Did I come back to life?

404
00:21:55,166 --> 00:21:56,375
[KAZUKI]
Toi!

405
00:21:56,458 --> 00:21:58,666
[TOI]
I understand.

406
00:21:58,750 --> 00:22:01,208
I would have saved Jinnai's life
if I were you, too.

407
00:22:02,583 --> 00:22:05,208
I'm just tired of this.

408
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:08,125
Toi.

409
00:22:08,208 --> 00:22:09,583
[thunder crashes]

410
00:22:09,666 --> 00:22:11,041
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
Dark Keppi.

411
00:22:11,125 --> 00:22:13,708
Why don't you take
every connection in the world

412
00:22:13,791 --> 00:22:15,875
-and tear them all to shreds?
-[DARK KEPPI] Dadadadadadada...

413
00:22:15,958 --> 00:22:18,458
[MALE VOICE]
Despair. Release.

414
00:22:19,458 --> 00:22:21,083
[exploding]

415
00:22:21,166 --> 00:22:22,541
-[DARK KEPPI] Dadadadadadadada.
-[gasps]

416
00:22:22,625 --> 00:22:23,958
[BOTH gasp]

417
00:22:24,041 --> 00:22:28,708
[DARK KEPPI]
Dadadadadadadada.

418
00:22:28,791 --> 00:22:30,458
Darkness!

419
00:22:30,541 --> 00:22:32,958
[gasping]

420
00:22:33,041 --> 00:22:35,000
I'm coming!
[grunts]

421
00:22:37,625 --> 00:22:39,125
[strained grunting]

422
00:22:41,375 --> 00:22:44,125
Let's cut off these pointless
connections of yours.

423
00:22:44,208 --> 00:22:45,791
Shall we?

424
00:22:45,875 --> 00:22:48,916
We can go outside of the circle,
together.

425
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:52,416
[KAZUKI grunts, gasps]

426
00:22:54,916 --> 00:22:57,875
[KAZUKI]
Toi!

